Note: Recommended Length is 15. There's no specific validation for the fax number.

companyName.description:
Contact person's company name.
Note: Recommended Length is 35. There's no specific validation for the company name.

stateTaxId.description: Specify State TaxID for the contact person.

fedralTaxId.description: Specify Fedral TaxId for the contact person.

Contact.description: Contact details for the Party such as Name, Email, PhoneNumber.

tollFreePhoneNumber.description:
Specify toll free phone number.
Example: XXXX7812

title.description: Specify the Title of the Contact.

ContactAncillaryDetail.description: Indicates additional contact details for the Party such as email and phone contact information.

streetLines.description:
This is a combination of number, street name, etc.
Note: At least one line is required and streetlines more than 3 will be ignored. Empty lines should not be included.

city.description:
This is a placeholder for City Name.
Note: This is conditional and not required in all the shipping requests. It is recommended for Express shipments for the most accurate ODA and OPA surcharges and not used for Ground/SmartPost.

stateOrProvinceCode.description:
This is a placeholder for State or Province code.
Note: This is conditional and not required in all the shipping requests. It is recommended for Express shipments for the most accurate ODA and OPA surcharges and not used for Ground/SmartPost.

postalCode.description:
This is placeholder for postal code.
Note: The postal code is required for postal-aware countries.

countryCode.description: This is the Two-letter country code. Click here to see Country Codes

residential.description:
Indicate whether this address is Residential as opposed to Commercial.
Valid Values: True or False.

Address.description: Descriptive data for a physical location. May be used as an actual physical address (place to which one could go), or as a container of "address parts" which should be handled as a unit (such as a city-state-ZIP combination within the US).

maskedData.description: Specifies the name of data elements/areas which may be suppressed from printing on labels.

regulatoryLabels.description: Specifies details needed to generate any label artifacts required due to regulatory requirements

CustomerSpecifiedLabelDetail.description: Allows customer-specified control of label content

DocTabContent.description: Specifies details of doc tab content, If provided, thermal documents will include specified doc tab content. If omitted, document will be produced without doc tab content.

clearanceFacilityLocationId.description: Specifies the clearance facility location id.

currency.description: Three-character ISO currency code (e.g. USD, CAD, EUR, JPY, etc.)

Money.description: This is commodity value used for Customs declaration.

amount.description:
This is commodity value in amount used for Customs declaration.
Max limit: 7 digits before decimal.

currency.description: This is the currency of the commodity value used for Customs declaration.Click here to see Currency Codes

Money_2.description: This is commodity value used for Customs declaration.

TransborderDistributionDetail.description: Specifies attributes of a shipment whithin a transborder distribution.

importerOfRecord.description: The descriptive data for the importer of Record for the shipment and their physical address, contact and account number information.

insuranceCharges.description: Amount paid to a third party for the purpose of insuring this shipment against damage or loss.  Used to calculate estimated duties and taxes

commodities.description: Indicates the details about the dutiable packages. Maximum upto 999 commodities per shipment.

brokers.description:
Conditional.
Specify Broker information only if you are using Broker Select Option for your shipment.To be considered a valid, a country code must be specified in addition to one of the following address items: postal code, city, or location id.

clearanceBrokerage.description: Specifies the type of brokerage to be applied to a shipment.

freightOnValue.description: Identifies responsibilities with respect to loss, damage, etc.

CustomsClearanceDetail.description: Required for International and intra-country Shipments. Information about this package that only applies to an international (export) shipment or return.

description.description: Specify additional description about customs options. This is a required field when the Type is OTHER.

type.description: Specify the reason for a global return, as recognized by Customs.

CustomsOptionDetail.description: Customs Option Detail, type must be indicated for each occurrence

tins.description: This is the tax identification number details.

deliveryInstructions.description:
Used with Ground Home Delivery and Freight.
Example: FRONT DOOR

tins.description: This is the tax identification number details.

Party_2.description: Attributes for a Party to a transaction including the physical address, contact information, and account number information.

tins.description: Used for adding the tax id

paymentType.description:
Specify the payment Type.
Note: This is required for Express, Ground and SmartPost shipments.
The payment type COLLECT is applicable only for Ground shipments.

Payment.description: Details about who and how the shipment will be paid for. 'payor' is optional when 'paymentType' provided is SENDER.

Payor.description: Information about the person who is paying for the shipment.  Not applicable for credit card payment.

b13AFilingOption.description: Specify the filing option being exercised. Required for non-document shipments originating in Canada destinated for any country other than Canada, the United States, Puerto Rico, or the U.S. Virgin Islands.

exportComplianceStatement.description:
For shipments requiring an EEI, enter the ITN number received from AES when you filed your shipment or the FTR (Foreign Trade Regulations) exemption number.The proper format for an ITN number is AES XYYYYMMDDNNNNNN where YYYYMMDD is date and NNNNNN are numbers generated by the AES.
Note: The ITN or FTR exemption number you submit in the Ship request prints on the international shipping label.

permitNumber.description: This is a Permit Number. This field is applicable only to Canada export non-document shipments of any value to any destination. No special characters are allowed.

ExportDetail.description: Conditional. Export Detail Used for US or CA exports.

endUser.description: Specify End User name. Its is required if StatementTypes is entered as DEPARTMENT_OF_STATE.

statementTypes.description: Specify appropriate destination control statement type(s), Also make sure to specify destination country and end user.

destinationCountries.description: Specify DCS shipment destination country. You may enter up to four country codes in this element. Up to 11 alphanumeric characters are allowed.

DestinationControlDetail.description:
VERY IMPORTANT: Specify appropriate destinationcontrol statement type(s),Valid values: DEPARTMENT_OF_COMMERCE, DEPARTMENT_OF_STATE
Be sure to also specify destination country and enduser.

numberOfPieces.description: Indicates the number of pieces associated with the commodity. Number of pieces cannot be a negative value or exceed 9,999.

description.description: This is the commodity description. Maximum allowed 450 characters.

countryOfManufacture.description: This is commodity country of manufacture. This is required for International shipments. Maximum allowed length is 4.

quantity.description: This is the units quantity (using quantityUnits as the unit of measure) per commodity. This is used to estimate duties and taxes.

quantityUnits.description: This is the unit of measure for the units quantity. This is used to estimate duties and taxes.

commodityId.description: Value used to identify a commodity description; must be unique within the containing shipment.

broker.description: 'The descriptive data for the broker for the shipment and their physical address, contact and account number information.'

type.description: Identifies the type of Broker.

customDocumentDetails.description: Specifies the child reference number report detail for consolidated SoldTo summary report detail.

The unique location identifier

clearanceNumber.description:

inclusionSpecifications.description: Specifies which kinds of shipments will be processed by this distribution location.

DistributionLocations.description:
Specifies the distribution locations for consolidation.
Mandatory for International Ground Distribution.
